As part of efforts by individuals, organisations and agencies to put an end to the raging covid 19 pandemic, Rotary club of Lekki Golden, District 9110, Lagos in collaboration with Winifred Igweonwu Foundation has donated items worth millions of Naira to the Lagos State University Teaching Hospital (LASUTH) in Lagos. President of the Rotary club, Mrs Winifred Igweonwu said that the gesture was borne out of the need to support the fight against the global pandemic as it continues to decimate the world economy and population.  Igweonwu, who doubles as the Chairperson/Chief Executive Officer (CEO) of Winifred Igweonwu Foundation (WIF) added that the donation was made possible with collaboration with the Rotary club.  Some.of the items donated by the foundation include; Hand Sanitizers, Medical Protective Gloves, Antiseptic Disinfectants, Infrared Thermometers, customized Bedsheets and Bedspreads.  Speaking further, she maintained that  the fear of further spread of the virus elicited the prompt intervention of the foundation.  In her release made available to our correspondent, Igweonwu  stated further that the yet growing economy in Nigeria is struggling to contain the few cases so far identified and to control further spread aligns with one of Rotary’s six focus Areas which is disease prevention and control.  Her words, “So our club, the Rotary Club of Lekki Golden, in collaboration with Winifred Igweonwu Foundation felt there is a need to support the fight against the covid 19 virus in whatever little way we can.  “For this reason, we have here presented this token (Bulks of: Hand Sanitizers, Medical Protective Gloves, Antiseptic Disinfectants, Infra-red Thermometers, customized Bedsheets and Bedspreads) in our subtle might, as our way of supporting the good work being done by your Hospital and to encourage all the healthcare workers and the government not to relent in the fight.” 